# Notification system rules

Use these whenever adding or changing **in-app** (`realtime_events`) or **remote push** behavior, copy, or UI. (Scheduled **local OS** reminders may keep using `NotificationService.show` / scheduler, but still pull copy from the same copy source and keep screens thin.)

## Project paths (this repo)

| Concept | Location |
| -------- | -------- |
| Copy (event → Moody string) | `lib/core/notifications/notification_copy.dart` |
| Send / local plugin | `lib/core/services/notification_service.dart` |
| In-app load / streams | `lib/features/realtime/application/realtime_service.dart` (and related) |

If a dedicated **inbox list** or **`NotificationCard`** widget is introduced under another path, this rule still applies — consolidate there instead of duplicating.

## Rules

### 1. Single source of truth

All notification **copy** lives in **`lib/core/notifications/notification_copy.dart`** (map / types keyed by event). **Never** hardcode the same strings in screens, repositories, or Edge code when the app should show that text — extend the Dart copy map (and wire from the single send path).

### 2. Single send function

All **Supabase `realtime_events` inserts** and **push-notify (or equivalent) Edge Function** calls must go through **one** API — canonical name: **`NotificationService.send()`** (implement on `NotificationService` or delegate internally if the name differs today).

- Do **not** call `supabase.from('realtime_events').insert(...)` from a screen.
- Do **not** invoke the push Edge Function from a screen.

One call should drive **both** in-app and push where applicable.

### 3. No notification logic in screens

Screens call the send API (and navigation only). **No** realtime subscriptions, FCM token lookups, or push HTTP in screen widgets for new work.

### 4. Reuse the card widget

One widget — **`NotificationCard`** (or the single shared row used by the notification centre) — for every place a notification row is shown. **Extend** that widget for new layouts; do **not** build one-off cards in feature screens.

### 5. No new tables or columns

Only **`realtime_events`** and **`push_tokens`** for notification persistence. If something seems to need another table, **stop and ask** the product owner first.

### 6. Fire and forget

Remote push must be **`try` / `catch`**, **not** `await`ed on the critical user path. A failed push must **not** block UI or surface as a user-visible error in the main flow.

### 7. Line budgets

When editing these files, **stay within** the caps; if a file is already over, **refactor in the same change** before growing behavior.

| File | Max lines |
| ----- | -----: |
| `notification_copy.dart` | 200 |
| `notification_service.dart` | 150 |
| Notification centre / inbox list screen (unified UI) | 300 |
| `notification_card.dart` | 100 |
